12:
Then I saw him open
 the sixth seal. A violent earthquake occurred;
 the sun turned black like sackcloth
 made of hair; the entire moon
 became like blood;

16:
They will no longer hunger;
they will no longer thirst;
the sun will no longer strike them,
nor will any scorching heat.

14:
The fruit you craved has left you.
All your splendid and glamorous things are gone;
they will never find them again.

22:
The sound of harpists, musicians,
flutists, and trumpeters
will never be heard in you again;
no craftsman of any trade
will ever be found in you again;
the sound of a mill
will never be heard in you again;

1:
Then I saw a new heaven and a new earth;
 for the first heaven and the first earth had passed away,
 and the sea was no more.

5:
Night will be no more;
 people will not need the light of a lamp or the light of the sun, because the Lord God will give them light,
 and they will reign forever and ever.
